50|$|Chapters on {{clothing}} {{are followed}} by a section on housing. Julius describes a <b>double</b> <b>roof</b> for dwellings, with an air gap between {{the inner and outer}} roof to reduce direct radiant heating. He describes ventilating machines in detail, including a cooling system using subterranean tubes and the Refrigerator (his own invention), and based on evaporative cooling.|$|E
